description: Numbers not divisible by p^p for any prime p.
comments: If n = Product p_i^e_i then p_i>e_i for all i.Complement of A100716; A129251(a(n)) = 0. - _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Apr 07 2007Density is 0.72199023441955... = prod(1 - p^-p) where p runs over the primes. [_Charles R Greathouse IV_, Jan 25 2012]A027748(a(n),k) <= A124010(a(n),k), 1<=k<=A001221(a(n)). [__Reinhard Zumkeller_, Apr 28 2012_]
links: R. Zumkeller, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
formula: a(n) ~ kn with k = 1/prod(1 - p^-p) = prod 1 + 1/(p^p - 1) = 1.3850602852..., where the product is over all primes p. [_Charles R Greathouse IV_, Jan 25 2012]
